  <name>AccessMate</name>
  <summary>Comprehensive accessibility assistant with speech recognition and text-to-speech</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      AccessMate is a powerful accessibility tool designed to help users with visual, hearing, 
      or motor impairments interact more effectively with their Linux desktop environment.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Advanced speech recognition with multiple engine support</li>
      <li>High-quality text-to-speech synthesis</li>
      <li>Screen reading capabilities</li>
      <li>Voice-controlled navigation</li>
      <li>Customizable accessibility profiles</li>
      <li>Integration with popular applications</li>
      <li>Keyboard shortcut management</li>
      <li>Audio feedback and notifications</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      AccessMate works seamlessly with existing assistive technologies and can be customized 
      to meet individual accessibility needs.
    </p>
  </description>
  
